# Image Filtering
Apply basic filters to base64 encoded images
## Installation
```
git clone https://github.com/kemalik/image-filtering.git
cd image-filtering
docker-compose up
```
## Usage
### Upload base64 encoded image
```
REQUEST
POST http://localhost:8000/api/images/
- base64_image: data:image/png;base64,

RESPONSE
{
    "id": 77,
    "image": "data:image/png;base64,",
    "creation_date": "2017-07-25T11:42:51.754054Z"
}

```
### Apply filter
```
REQUEST
POST http://localhost:8000/api/filter/
- iamge: 77
- filter: edge # one of {edge|red_tint|swirl}

RESPONSE
{
    "id": 52,
    "image": 77,
    "filter": "edge",
    "result": null,
    "status": "in_progress"
}

```
### Retrive resource
```
REQUEST
GET http://localhost:8000/api/filter/52/ # resource id

RESPOSE
{
    "id": 52,
    "image": 77,
    "filter": "edge",
    "result": 78,
    "status": "done"
}
```

### Retrive result
```
REQUEST
http://localhost:8000/api/images/78/ #

RESPONSE
{
    "id": 78,
    "image": "data:image/png;base64,",
    "creation_date": "2017-07-25T11:43:04.148268Z"
```
